The draw for the UEFA Nations League semi-finals was announced on Thursday night. Italy will tackle Spain, while Belgium will face France. UEFA disclosed this in a post via its website. The first semi-final tie between Italy and Spain will take place on 6 October 2021 at AC Milan’s San Siro Stadium. The tie between Belgium and France will take place on 7 October 2021 at the Juventus’s Allianz Stadium in Turin. The match for third place will take place on Sunday 10 October: Juventus Stadium, Turin (15:00 CET), while the final will take place on Sunday 10 October: San Siro, Milan (20:45 CET).